    "texto": "It is appropriate to speak of the artisans as possessed of wisdom (and not just \"skill\"), because the biblical writers share the understanding common to most traditional societies that the active form of wisdom is good work. Wisdom does not consist only in sound intellectual work; any activity that stands in a consistently productive relationship to the material world and nurtures the creative imagination qualifies as wise.",
